==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Actuary
<hw>Ac"tu*a*ry</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Actuaries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>actuarius</ets>
copyist, clerk, fr. <ets>actus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>agere</ets> to do,
act.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A registrar or clerk; --
used originally in courts of civil law jurisdiction, but in Europe used
for a clerk or registrar generally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The computing official of an insurance company; one
whose profession it is to calculate for insurance companies the risks
and premiums for life, fire, and other insurances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Actuate</ent>⟦br⟧
